metadata.name: I LOST 231$
metadata.description:
It all started with a $231 investment in PNUT. Drawn in by the hype and promises of massive returns, an investor put their money into the token, only to watch it crash almost immediately. That $231 vanished into thin air, leaving them frustrated and suspicious.

At first, they thought it was just bad luck, but as they dug deeper, they realized there might be more to the story. Online discussions revealed accusations of pump-and-dump schemes, shady marketing practices, and a complete lack of safeguards like KYC or AML.

What started as a small personal loss became the beginning of a much bigger battle. They decided to take legal action against PumpFun, the platform behind PNUT. Now, this $231 loss has escalated into a lawsuit that could bring major consequences, not just for PumpFun, but for the entire memecoin market.
